  1817. deleth from dalah; something swinging, i.e. the valve of a door: door (two-leaved), gate, leaf, lid. (In Psa. 141:3, dal, irreg.).
  1818. dam from damam (compare 'adam); blood (as that which when shed causes death) of man or an animal; by analogy, the juice of the grape; figuratively (especially in the plural) bloodshed (i.e. drops of blood): blood(-y, -guiltiness, (-thirsty), + innocent.
  1819. damah a primitive root; to compare; by implication, to resemble, liken, consider: compare, devise, (be) like(-n), mean, think, use similitudes.
  1820. damah a primitive root; to be dumb or silent; hence, to fail or perish; trans. to destroy: cease, be cut down (off), destroy, be brought to silence, be undone, X utterly.

  1824. dmiy or domiy; from damah; quiet: cutting off, rest, silence.

  1826. damam a prim root (compare daham, damah); to be dumb; by implication, to be astonished, to stop; also to perish: cease, be cut down (off), forbear, hold peace, quiet self, rest, be silent, keep (put to) silence, be (stand) still, tarry, wait.

  1931. huw' of which the feminine (beyond the Pentateuch) is hiyw; a primitive word, the third person pronoun singular, he (she or it); only expressed when emphatic or without a verb; also (intensively) self, or (especially with the article) the same; sometimes (as demonstrative) this or that; occasionally (instead of copula) as or are: he, as for her, him(-self), it, the same, she (herself), such, that (...it), these, they, this, those, which (is), who.

  1980. halak akin to yalak; a primitive root; to walk (in a great variety of applications, literally and figuratively): (all) along, apace, behave (self), come, (on) continually, be conversant, depart, + be eased, enter, exercise (self), + follow, forth, forward, get, go (about, abroad, along, away, forward, on, out, up and down), + greater, grow, be wont to haunt, lead, march, X more and more, move (self), needs, on, pass (away), be at the point, quite, run (along), + send, speedily, spread, still, surely, + tale-bearer, + travel(-ler), walk (abroad, on, to and fro, up and down, to places), wander, wax, (way-)faring man, X be weak, whirl.

  2181. zanah a primitive root (highly-fed and therefore wanton); to commit adultery (usually of the female, and less often of simple fornication, rarely of involuntary ravishment); figuratively, to commit idolatry (the Jewish people being regarded as the spouse of Jehovah): (cause to) commit fornication, X continually, X great, (be an, play the) harlot, (cause to be, play the) whore, (commit, fall to) whoredom, (cause to) go a-whoring, whorish.

  2616. chacad a primitive root; properly, perhaps to bow (the neck only (compare chanan) in courtesy to an equal), i.e. to be kind; also (by euphem. (compare barak), but rarely) to reprove: shew self merciful, put to shame.
  2617. checed from chacad; kindness; by implication (towards God) piety: rarely (by opposition) reproof, or (subject.) beauty: favour, good deed(-liness, -ness), kindly, (loving-)kindness, merciful (kindness), mercy, pity, reproach, wicked thing.

  2672. chatsab or chatseb; a primitive root; to cut or carve (wood), stone or other material); by implication, to hew, split, square, quarry, engrave: cut, dig, divide, grave, hew (out, -er), made, mason.

  2814. chashah a primitive root; to hush or keep quiet: hold peace, keep silence, be silent, (be) still.
  2815. Chashshuwb from chashab; intelligent; Chashshub, the name of two or three Israelites: Hashub, Hasshub.
  2816. chashowk (Aramaic) from a root corresponding to chashak; the dark: darkness.

  2818. chashach (Aramaic) a collateral root to one corresponding to chuwsh in the sense of readiness; to be necessary (from the idea of convenience) or (transitively) to need: careful, have need of.
  2819. chashchuwth from a root corresponding to chashach; necessity: be needful.
  2820. chasak a primitive root; to restrain or (reflex.) refrain; by implication, to refuse, spare, preserve; also (by interch. with chashak) to observe: assuage, X darken, forbear, hinder, hold back, keep (back), punish, refrain, reserve, spare, withhold.
  2821. chashak a primitive root; to be dark (as withholding light); transitively, to darken: be black, be (make) dark, darken, cause darkness, be dim, hide.
  2822. choshek from chashak; the dark; hence (literally) darkness; figuratively, misery, destruction, death, ignorance, sorrow, wickedness: dark(-ness), night, obscurity.

  2824. cheshkah from chashak; darkness: dark.
  2825. chashekah or chashekah; from chashak; darkness; figuratively, misery: darkness.

  2828. Chashum from the same as chashman; enriched; Chashum, the name of two or three Israelites: Hashum.

  2833. choshen from an unused root probably meaning to contain or sparkle; perhaps a pocket (as holding the Urim and Thummim), or rich (as containing gems), used only of the gorget of the highpriest: breastplate.
  2834. chasaph a primitive root; to strip off, i.e. generally to make naked (for exertion or in disgrace), to drain away or bail up (a liquid): make bare, clean, discover, draw out, take, uncover.
  2835. chasiph from chasaph; properly, drawn off, i.e. separated; hence, a small company (as divided from the rest): little flock.
  2836. chashaq a primitive root; to cling, i.e. join, (figuratively) to love, delight in; elliptically (or by interchangeable for chasak) to deliver: have a delight, (have a) desire, fillet, long, set (in) love.
  2837. chesheq from chashaq; delight: desire, pleasure.
  2838. chashuq or chashuwq; past participle of chashaq; attached, i.e. a fence-rail or rod connecting the posts or pillars: fillet.
  2839. chishshuq from chashaq; conjoined, i.e. a wheel-spoke or rod connecting the hub with the rim: felloe.
  2840. chishshur from an unused root meaning to bind together; combined, i.e. the nave or hub of a wheel (as holding the spokes together): spoke.
  2841. chashrah from the same as chishshur; properly, a combination or gathering, i.e. of watery clouds: dark.
  2842. chashash by variation for qash; dry grass: chaff.
  2843. Chushathiy patronymically from Chuwshah; a Chushathite or descendant of Chushah: Hushathite.
  2844. chath from chathath; concretely, crushed; also afraid; abstractly, terror: broken, dismayed, dread, fear.
  2845. Cheth from chathath; terror; Cheth, an aboriginal Canaanite: Heth.
  2846. chathah a primitive root; to lay hold of; especially to pick up fire: heap, take (away).
  2847. chittah from chathath; fear: terror.
  2848. chittuwl from chathal; swathed, i.e. a bandage: roller.
  2849. chathchath from chath; terror: fear.
  2850. Chittiy patronymically from Cheth; a Chittite, or descendant of Cheth: Hittite, Hittities.

  2859. chathan a primitive root; to give (a daughter) away in marriage; hence (generally) to contract affinity by marriage: join in affinity, father in law, make marriages, mother in law, son in law.
  2860. chathan from chathan; a relative by marriage (especially through the bride); figuratively, a circumcised child (as a species of religious espousal): bridegroom, husband, son in law.

  2862. chathaph a primitive root; to clutch: take away.

  2864. chathar a primitive root; to force a passage, as by burglary; figuratively, with oars: dig (through), row.
  2865. chathath a primitive root; properly, to prostrate; hence, to break down, either (literally) by violence, or (figuratively) by confusion and fear: abolish, affright, be (make) afraid, amaze, beat down, discourage, (cause to) dismay, go down, scare, terrify.
  2866. chathath from chathath; dismay: casting down.

  2873. tabach a primitive root; to slaughter (animals or men): kill, (make) slaughter, slay.

  2875. Tebach the same as tebach; massacre; Tebach, the name of a Mesopotamian and of an Israelite: Tebah.

  2896. towb from towb; good (as an adjective) in the widest sense; used likewise as a noun, both in the masculine and the feminine, the singular and the plural (good, a good or good thing, a good man or woman; the good, goods or good things, good men or women), also as an adverb (well): beautiful, best, better, bountiful, cheerful, at ease, X fair (word), (be in) favour, fine, glad, good (deed, -lier, -liest, -ly, -ness, -s), graciously, joyful, kindly, kindness, liketh (best), loving, merry, X most, pleasant, + pleaseth, pleasure, precious, prosperity, ready, sweet, wealth, welfare, (be) well ((-favoured)).
  2897. Towb the same as towb; good; Tob, a region apparently East of the Jordan: Tob.
  2898. tuwb from towb; good (as a noun), in the widest sense, especially goodness (superlative concretely, the best), beauty, gladness, welfare: fair, gladness, good(-ness, thing, -s), joy, go well with.

  2901. tavah a primitive root; to spin: spin.
  2902. tuwach a primitive root; to smear, especially with lime: daub, overlay, plaister, smut.
  2903. towphaphah from an unusued root meaning to go around or bind; a fillet for the forehead: frontlet.
  2904. tuwl a primitive root; to pitch over or reel; hence (transitively) to cast down or out: carry away, (utterly) cast (down, forth, out), send out.

  2911. tchown from tachan; a hand mill; hence, a millstone: to grind.

  2913. tachanah from tachan; a hand mill; hence (figuratively) chewing: grinding.

  2915. tiyach from (the equiv. of) tuwach; mortar or plaster: daubing.
  2916. tiyt from an unused root meaning apparently to be sticky (rath. perb. a demon. from tuw', through the idea of dirt to be swept away); mud or clay; figuratively, calamity: clay, dirt, mire.
  2917. tiyn (Aramaic) perhaps, by interchange, for a word corresponding to tiyt; clay: miry.
  2918. tiyrah feminine of (an equivalent to) tuwr; a wall; hence, a fortress or a hamlet: (goodly) castle, habitation, palace, row.
  2919. tal from talal; dew (as covering vegetation): dew.
  2920. tal (Aramaic) the same as tal: dew.

  2922. tla' apparently from tala' in the (orig.) sense of covering (for protection); a lamb (compare taleh): lamb.

  2947. tephach from taphach; a spread of the hand, i.e. a palm- breadth (not "span" of the fingers); architecturally, a corbel (as a supporting palm): coping, hand-breadth.

  2953. tphar (Aramaic) from a root corresponding to tsaphar, and meaning the same as tsipporen; a finger-nail; also a hoof or claw: nail.

  2968. ya'ab a primitive root; to desire: long.

  2975. y`or of Egyptian origin; a channel, e.g. a fosse, canal, shaft; specifically the Nile, as the one river of Egypt, including its collateral trenches; also the Tigris, as the main river of Assyria: brook, flood, river, stream.

  3027. yad a primitive word; a hand (the open one (indicating power, means, direction, etc.), in distinction from kaph, the closed one); used (as noun, adverb, etc.) in a great variety of applications, both literally and figuratively, both proximate and remote (as follows): (+ be) able, X about, + armholes, at, axletree, because of, beside, border, X bounty, + broad, (broken-)handed, X by, charge, coast, + consecrate, + creditor, custody, debt, dominion, X enough, + fellowship, force, X from, hand(-staves, -y work), X he, himself, X in, labour, + large, ledge, (left-)handed, means, X mine, ministry, near, X of, X order, ordinance, X our, parts, pain, power, X presumptuously, service, side, sore, state, stay, draw with strength, stroke, + swear, terror, X thee, X by them, X themselves, X thine own, X thou, through, X throwing, + thumb, times, X to, X under, X us, X wait on, (way-)side, where, + wide, X with (him, me, you), work, + yield, X yourselves.
  3028. yad (Aramaic) corresponding to yad: hand, power.
  3029. yda' (Aramaic) corresponding to yadah; to praise: (give) thank(-s).
  3030. Yidalah of uncertain derivation; Jidalah, a place in Palestine: Idalah.
  3031. Yidbash from the same as dbash; perhaps honeyed; Jidbash, an Israelite: Idbash.
  3032. yadad a primitive root; properly, to handle (compare yadah), i.e. to throw, e.g. lots: cast.
  3033. ydiduwth from ydiyd; properly, affection; concretely, a darling object: dearly beloved.
  3034. yadah a primitive root; used only as denominative from yad; literally, to use (i.e. hold out) the hand; physically, to throw (a stone, an arrow) at or away; especially to revere or worship (with extended hands); intensively, to bemoan (by wringing the hands): cast (out), (make) confess(-ion), praise, shoot, (give) thank(-ful, -s, -sgiving).

  3408. Yriy`owth plural of yriy`ah; curtains; Jerioth, an Israelitess: Jerioth.
  3409. yarek from an unused root meaning to be soft; the thigh (from its fleshy softness); by euphem. the generative parts; figuratively, a shank, flank, side: X body, loins, shaft, side, thigh.
  3410. yarka' (Aramaic) corresponding to yrekah; a thigh: thigh.
  3411. yrekah feminine of yarek; properly, the flank; but used only figuratively, the rear or recess: border, coast, part, quarter, side.
  3412. Yarmuwth from ruwm; elevation; Jarmuth, the name of two places in Palestine: Jarmuth.
  3413. Yremay from ruwm; elevated; Jeremai, an Israelite: -Jeremai.
  3414. Yirmyah or Yirmyahuw; from ruwm and Yahh; Jah will rise; Jirmejah, the name of eight or nine Israelites: Jeremiah.
  3415. yara` a primitive root; properly, to be broken up (with any violent action) i.e. (figuratively) to fear: be grevious (only Isa. 15:4; the rest belong to ra`a`).
  3416. Yirp'el from rapha' and 'el; God will heal; Jirpeel, a place in Palestine: Irpeel.
  3417. yaraq a primitive root; to spit: X but, spit.
  3418. yereq from yaraq (in the sense of vacuity of color); properly, pallor, i.e. hence, the yellowish green of young and sickly vegetation; concretely, verdure, i.e. grass or vegetation: grass, green (thing).
  3419. yaraq from the same as yereq; properly, green; concretely, a vegetable: green, herbs.
  3420. yeraqown from yereq; paleness, whether of persons (from fright), or of plants (from drought): greenish, yellow.
  3421. Yorq`am from ruwq and `am; people will be poured forth; Jorkeam, a place in Palestine: Jorkeam.
  3422. yraqraq from the same as yereq; yellowishness: -greenish, yellow.
  3423. yarash or yaresh; a primitive root; to occupy (by driving out previous tenants, and possessing in their place); by implication, to seize, to rob, to inherit; also to expel, to impoverish, to ruin: cast out, consume, destroy, disinherit, dispossess, drive(-ing) out, enjoy, expel, X without fail, (give to, leave for) inherit(-ance, -or) + magistrate, be (make) poor, come to poverty, (give to, make to) possess, get (have) in (take) possession, seize upon, succeed, X utterly.
  3424. yreshah from yarash; occupancy: possession.
  3425. yrushah from yarash; something occupied; a conquest; also a patrimony: heritage, inheritance, possession.
  3426. yesh perhaps from an unused root meaning to stand out, or exist; entity; used adverbially or as a copula for the substantive verb (hayah); there is or are (or any other form of the verb to be, as may suit the connection): (there) are, (he, it, shall, there, there may, there shall, there should) be, thou do, had, hast, (which) hath, (I, shalt, that) have, (he, it, there) is, substance, it (there) was, (there) were, ye will, thou wilt, wouldest.
  3427. yashab a primitive root; properly, to sit down (specifically as judge. in ambush, in quiet); by implication, to dwell, to remain; causatively, to settle, to marry: (make to) abide(-ing), continue, (cause to, make to) dwell(-ing), ease self, endure, establish, X fail, habitation, haunt, (make to) inhabit(-ant), make to keep (house), lurking, X marry(-ing), (bring again to) place, remain, return, seat, set(- tle), (down-)sit(-down, still, -ting down, -ting (place) -uate), take, tarry.
  3428. Yesheb'ab from yashab and 'ab; seat of (his) father; Jeshebab, an Israelite: Jeshebeab.
  3429. Yosheb bash-Shebeth from the active participle of yashab and shebeth, with a preposition and the article interposed; sitting in the seat; Josheb-bash-Shebeth, an Israelite: that sat in the seat.
  3430. Yishbow b-Nob from yashab and Nob, with a pronominal suffix and a preposition interposed; his dwelling (is) in Nob; Jishbo-be-Nob, a Philistine: Ishbi-benob (from the margin).
  3431. Yishbach from shabach; he will praise; Jishbach, an Israelite: Ishbah.
  3432. Yashubiy patronymically from Yashuwb; a Jashubite, or descendant of Jashub: Jashubites.
  3433. Yashubiy Lechem from shuwb and lechem; returner of bread; Jashubi-Lechem, an Israelite: Jashubi-lehem. (Prob. the text should be pointed Yoshbev Lechem, and rendered "(they were) inhabitants of Lechem," i.e. of Bethlehem (by contraction). Compare Lachmiy).
  3434. Yashob`am from shuwb and `am; people will return; Jashobam, the name of two or three Israelites: Jashobeam.
  3435. Yishbaq from an unused root corresponding to shbaq; he will leave; Jishbak, a son of Abraham: Ishbak.
  3436. Yoshbqashah from yashab and qasheh; a hard seat; Joshbekashah, an Israelite: Joshbekashah.
  3437. Yashuwb or Yashiyb; from shuwb; he will return; Jashub, the name of two Israelites: Jashub.
  3438. Yishvah from shavah; he will level; Jishvah, an Israelite: -Ishvah, Isvah.
  3439. Yshowchayah from the same as yeshach and Yahh; Jah will empty; Jeshochajah, an Israelite: Jeshoaiah.
  3440. Yishviy from shavah; level; Jishvi, the name of two Israelites: Ishuai, Ishvi, Isui, Jesui.
  3441. Yishviy patronymically from Yishviy; a Jishvite (collectively) or descendants of Jishvi: Jesuites.
  3442. Yeshuwa` for Yhowshuwa`; he will save; Jeshua, the name of ten Israelites, also of a place in Palestine: Jeshua.

  3444. yshuw`ah feminine passive participle of yasha`; something saved, i.e. (abstractly) deliverance; hence, aid, victory, prosperity: deliverance, health, help(-ing), salvation, save, saving (health), welfare.
  3445. yeshach from an unused root meaning to gape (as the empty stomach); hunger: casting down.
  3446. Yischaq from Shachatsowm; he will laugh; Jischak, the heir of Abraham: Isaac. Compare Yitschaq.
  3447. yashat a primitive root; to extend: hold out.
  3448. Yishay by Aramaic Iyshay; from the same as yesh; extant; Jishai, David's father: Jesse.
  3449. Yishshiyah or Yishshiyahuw; from nashah and Yahh; Jah will lend; Jishshijah, the name of five Israelites: Ishiah, Isshiah, Ishijah, Jesiah.

  3454. Yshiyshay from yashiysh; aged; Jeshishai, an Israelite: Jeshishai.
  3455. yasam a prim root; to place; intransitively, to be placed: be put (set).
  3456. yasham a primitive root; to lie waste: be desolate.
  3457. Yishma' from yasham; desolate; Jishma, an Israelite: -Ishma.
  3458. Yishma`e'l from shama` and 'el; God will hear; Jishmael, the name of Abraham's oldest son, and of five Israelites: Ishmael.
  3459. Yishma`e'liy patronymically from Yishma`e'l; a Jishmaelite or descendant of Jishmael: Ishmaelite.
  3460. Yishma`yah or Yishmacyahuw; from shama` and Yahh; Jah will hear; Jishmajah, the name of two Israelites: Ishmaiah.
  3461. Yishmray from shamar; preservative; Jishmerai, an Israelite: Ishmerai.
  3462. yashen a primitive root; properly, to be slack or languid, i.e. (by implication) sleep (figuratively, to die); also to grow old, stale or inveterate: -old (store), remain long, (make to) sleep.
  3463. yashen from yashen; sleepy: asleep, (one out of) sleep(-eth, -ing), slept.
  3464. Yashen the same as yashen; Jashen, an Israelite: Jashen.
  3465. yashan from yashen; old: old.
  3466. Yshanah feminine of yashan; Jeshanah, a place in Palestine: Jeshanah.
  3467. yasha` a primitive root; properly, to be open, wide or free, i.e. (by implication) to be safe; causatively, to free or succor: X at all, avenging, defend, deliver(-er), help, preserve, rescue, be safe, bring (having) salvation, save(-iour), get victory.
  3468. yesha` or yeshai; from yasha`; liberty, deliverance, prosperity: safety, salvation, saving.
  3469. Yish`iy from yasha`; saving; Jishi, the name of four Israelites: Ishi.
  3470. Ysha`yah or Yshayahuw; from yasha` and Yahh; Jah has saved; Jeshajah, the name of seven Israelites: Isaiah, Jesaiah, Jeshaiah.
  3471. yashpheh from an unused root meaning to polish; a gem supposed to be jasper (from the resemblance in name): jasper.

  3473. Yishpan probably from the same as shaphan; he will hide; Jishpan, an Israelite: Ishpan.
  3474. yashar a primitive root; to be straight or even; figuratively, to be (causatively, to make) right, pleasant, prosperous: direct, fit, seem good (meet), + please (will), be (esteem, go) right (on), bring (look, make, take the) straight (way), be upright(-ly).
  3475. Yesher from yashar; the right; Jesher, an Israelite: -Jesher.
  3476. yosher from yashar; the right: equity, meet, right, upright(-ness).
  3477. yashar from yashar; straight (literally or figuratively): convenient, equity, Jasher, just, meet(-est), + pleased well right(-eous), straight, (most) upright(-ly, -ness).
  3478. Yisra'el from sarah and 'el; he will rule as God; Jisrael, a symbolical name of Jacob; also (typically) of his posterity: Israel.
  3479. Yisra'el (Aramaic) corresponding to Yisra'el: Israel.
  3480. Ysar'elah by variation from yashar and 'el with directive enclitic; right towards God; Jesarelah, an Israelite: Jesharelah.
  3481. Yisr'eliy patronymically from Yisra'el; a Jisreelite or descendant of Jisrael: of Israel, Israelite.
  3482. Yisr'eliyth feminine of Yisr'eliy; a Jisreelitess or female descendant of Jisrael: Israelitish.
  3483. yishrah feminine or yashar; rectitude: uprightness.
  3484. Yshuruwn from yashar; upright; Jeshurun, a symbol. name for Israel: Jeshurun.
  3485. Yissaskar (strictly yis-saws-kawr'); from nasa' and sakar; he will bring a reward; Jissaskar, a son of Jacob: Issachar.
  3486. yashesh from an unused root meaning to blanch; gray-haired, i.e. an aged man: stoop for age.
  3487. yath (Aramaic) corresponding to 'eth; a sign of the object of a verb: + whom.
  3488. ythiyb (Aramaic) corresponding to yashab; to sit or dwell: -dwell, (be) set, sit.
  3489. yathed from an unused root meaning to pin through or fast; a peg: nail, paddle, pin, stake.
  3490. yathowm from an unused root meaning to be lonely; a bereaved person: fatherless (child), orphan.
  3491. yathuwr passive participle of yathar; properly, what is left, i.e. (by implication) a gleaning: range.
  3492. Yattiyr from yathar; redundant; Jattir, a place in Palestine: Jattir.
  3493. yattiyr (Aramaic) corresponding to Yattiyr; preeminent; as an adverb, very: exceeding(-ly), excellent.
  3494. Yithlah probably from talah; it will hang, i.e. be high; Jithlah, a place in Palestine: Jethlah.
  3495. Yithmah from the same as yathowm; orphanage; Jithmah, an Israelite: Ithmah.
  3496. Yathniy'el from an unused root meaning to endure, and 'el; continued of God; Jathniel, an Israelite: Jathniel.
  3497. Yithnan from the same as tanniyn; extensive; Jithnan, a place in Palestine: Ithnan.
  3498. yathar a primitive root; to jut over or exceed; by implication, to excel; (intransitively) to remain or be left; causatively, to leave, cause to abound, preserve: excel, leave (a remnant), left behind, too much, make plenteous, preserve, (be, let) remain(-der, -ing, - nant), reserve, residue, rest.
  3499. yether from yathar; properly, an overhanging, i.e. (by implication) an excess, superiority, remainder; also a small rope (as hanging free): + abundant, cord, exceeding, excellancy(-ent), what they leave, that hath left, plentifully, remnant, residue, rest, string, with.
  3500. Yether the same as yether; Jether, the name of five or six Israelites and of one Midianite: Jether, Jethro. Compare Yithrow.
  3501. Yithra' by variation for yithrah; Jithra, an Israelite (or Ishmaelite): Ithra.
  3502. yithrah feminine of yether; properly, excellence, i.e. (by implication) wealth: abundance, riches.
  3503. Yithrow from yether with pron. suffix; his excellence; Jethro, Moses' father-in-law: Jethro. Compare Yether.
  3504. yithrown from yathar; preeminence, gain: better, excellency(-leth), profit(-able).
  3505. Yithriy patronymically from Yether; a Jithrite or descendant of Jether: Ithrite.
  3506. Yithran from yathar; excellent; Jithran, the name of an Edomite and of an Israelite: Ithran.
  3507. Yithr`am from yether and `am; excellence of people; Jithream, a son of David: Ithream.
  3508. yothereth feminine active participle of yathar; the lobe or flap of the liver (as if redundant or outhanging): caul.
  3509. Ytheyh of uncertain derivation; Jetheth, an Edomite: -Jetheth.
  3510. ka'ab a primitive root; properly, to feel pain; by implication, to grieve; figuratively, to spoil: grieving, mar, have pain, make sad (sore), (be) sorrowful.
  3511. k'eb from ka'ab; suffering (physical or mental), adversity: grief, pain, sorrow.
  3512. ka'ah a primitive root; to despond: causatively, to deject: broken, be grieved, make sad.
  3513. kabad or kabed; a primitive root; to be heavy, i.e. in a bad sense (burdensome, severe, dull) or in a good sense (numerous, rich, honorable; causatively, to make weighty (in the same two senses): abounding with, more grievously afflict, boast, be chargeable, X be dim, glorify, be (make) glorious (things), glory, (very) great, be grievous, harden, be (make) heavy, be heavier, lay heavily, (bring to, come to, do, get, be had in) honour (self), (be) honourable (man), lade, X more be laid, make self many, nobles, prevail, promote (to honour), be rich, be (go) sore, stop.
  3514. kobed from kabad; weight, multitude, vehemence: -grievousness, heavy, great number.
  3515. kabed from kabad; heavy; figuratively in a good sense (numerous) or in a bad sense (severe, difficult, stupid): (so) great, grievous, hard(-ened), (too) heavy(-ier), laden, much, slow, sore, thick.
  3516. kabed the same as kabed; the liver (as the heaviest of the viscera): liver.
  3517. kbeduth feminine of kabed; difficulty: X heavily.
  3518. kabah a primitive root; to expire or (causatively) to extinguish (fire, light, anger): go (put) out, quench.
  3519. kabowd rarely kabod; from kabad; properly, weight, but only figuratively in a good sense, splendor or copiousness: glorious(-ly), glory, honour(-able).
  3520. kbuwddah irreg. feminine passive participle of kabad; weightiness, i.e. magnificence, wealth: carriage, all glorious, stately.
  3521. Kabuwl from the same as kebel in the sense of limitation; sterile; Cabul, the name of two places in Palestine: Cabul.
  3522. Kabbown from an unused root meaning to heap up; hilly; Cabon, a place in Palestine: Cabbon.
  3523. kbiyr from kabar in the original sense of plaiting; a matrass (of intertwined materials): pillow.
  3524. kabbiyr from kabar; vast, whether in extent (figuratively, of power, mighty; of time, aged), or in number, many: + feeble, mighty, most, much, strong, valiant.
  3525. kebel from an unused root meaning to twine or braid together; a fetter: fetter.
  3526. kabac a primitive root; to trample; hence, to wash (properly, by stamping with the feet), whether literal (including the fulling process) or figurative: fuller, wash(-ing).
  3527. kabar a primitive root; properly, to plait together, i.e. (figuratively) to augment (especially in number or quantity, to accumulate): in abundance, multiply.
  3528. kbar from kabar; properly, extent of time, i.e. a great while; hence, long ago, formerly, hitherto: already, (seeing that which), now.
  3529. Kbar the same as kbar; length; Kebar, a river of Mesopotamia: Chebar. Compare Chabowr.
  3530. kibrah feminine of kbar; properly, length, i.e. a measure (of uncertain dimension): X little.
  3531. kbarah from kabar in its original sense; a sieve (as netted): sieve.
  3532. kebes from an unused root meaning to dominate; a ram (just old enough to butt): lamb, sheep.
  3533. kabash a primitive root; to tread down; hence, negatively, to disregard; positively, to conquer, subjugate, violate: bring into bondage, force, keep under, subdue, bring into subjection.
  3534. kebesh from kabash; a footstool (as trodden upon): -footstool.
  3535. kibsah or kabsah; feminine of kebes; a ewe: (ewe) lamb.
  3536. kibshan from kabash; a smelting furnace (as reducing metals): furnace.
  3537. kad from an unused root meaning to deepen; properly, a pail; but generally of earthenware; a jar for domestic purposes: barrel, pitcher.
  3538. kdab (Aramaic) from a root corresponding to kazab; false: -lying.
  3539. kadkod from the same as kad in the sense of striking fire from a metal forged; a sparkling gem, probably the ruby: agate.
  3540. Kdorla`omer of foreign origin; Kedorlaomer, an early Persian king: Chedorlaomer.
  3541. koh from the prefix k and huw'; properly, like this, i.e. by implication, (of manner) thus (or so); also (of place) here (or hither); or (of time) now: also, here, + hitherto, like, on the other side, so (and much), such, on that manner, (on) this (manner, side, way, way and that way), + mean while, yonder.
  3542. kah (Aramaic) corresponding to koh: hitherto.
  3543. kahah a primitive root; to be weak, i.e. (figuratively) to despond (causatively, rebuke), or (of light, the eye) to grow dull: darken, be dim, fail, faint, restrain, X utterly.
  3544. keheh from kahah; feeble, obscure: somewhat dark, darkish, wax dim, heaviness, smoking.
  3545. kehah feminine of keheh; properly, a weakening; figuratively, alleviation, i.e. cure: healing.
  3546. khal (Aramaic) a root corresponding to yakol and kuwl; to be able: be able, could.
  3547. kahan a primitive root, apparently meaning to mediate in religious services; but used only as denominative from kohen; to officiate as a priest; figuratively, to put on regalia: deck, be (do the office of a, execute the, minister in the) priest('s office).
  3548. kohen active participle of kahan; literally, one officiating, a priest; also (by courtesy) an acting priest (although a layman): chief ruler, X own, priest, prince, principal officer.
  3549. kahen (Aramaic) corresponding to kohen: priest.
  3550. khunnah from kahan; priesthood: priesthood, priest's office.
  3551. kav (Aramaic) from a root corresponding to lahag in the sense of piercing; a window (as a perforation): window.
  3552. Kuwb of foreign derivation; Kub, a country near Egypt: Chub.
  3553. kowba` from an unused root meaning to be high or rounded; a helmet (as arched): helmet. Compare qowba`.
  3554. kavah a primitive root; properly, to prick or penetrate; hence, to blister (as smarting or eating into): burn.
  3555. kviyah from kavah; a branding: burning.
  3556. kowkab probably from the same as Kabbown (in the sense of rolling) or kavah (in the sense of blazing); a star (as round or as shining); figuratively, a prince: star((-gazer)).
  3557. kuwl a primitive root; properly, to keep in; hence, to measure; figuratively, to maintain (in various senses): (be able to, can) abide, bear, comprehend, contain, feed, forbearing, guide, hold(-ing in), nourish(-er), be present, make provision, receive, sustain, provide sustenance (victuals).
  3558. kuwmaz from an unused root meaning to store away; a jewel (probably gold beads): tablet.
  3559. kuwn a primitive root; properly, to be erect (i.e. stand perpendicular); hence (causatively) to set up, in a great variety of applications, whether literal (establish, fix, prepare, apply), or figurative (appoint, render sure, proper or prosperous): certain(-ty), confirm, direct, faithfulness, fashion, fasten, firm, be fitted, be fixed, frame, be meet, ordain, order, perfect, (make) preparation, prepare (self), provide, make provision, (be, make) ready, right, set (aright, fast, forth), be stable, (e-)stablish, stand, tarry, X very deed.
  3560. Kuwn probably from kuwn; established; Kun, a place in Syria: Chun.
  3561. kavvan from kuwn; something prepared, i.e. a sacrificial wafer: cake.
  3562. Kownanyahuw from kuwn and Yahh; Jah has sustained; Conanjah, the name of two Israelites: Conaniah, Cononiah. Compare Knanyah.
  3563. kowc from an unused root meaning to hold together; a cup (as a container), often figuratively, a lot (as if a potion); also some unclean bird, probably an owl (perhaps from the cup-like cavity of its eye): cup, (small) owl. Compare kiyc.
  3564. kuwr from an unused root meaning properly, to dig through; a pot or furnace (as if excavated): furnace. Compare kiyr.
  3565. Kowr`Ashan from kuwr and `ashan; furnace of smoke; Cor-Ashan, a place in Palestine: Chor-ashan.
  3566. Kowresh or (Ezra 1:1 (last time),2) Koresh; from the Persians; Koresh (or Cyrus), the Persian king: Cyrus.
  3567. Kowresh (Aramaic) corresponding to Kowresh: Cyrus.
  3568. Kuwsh probably of foreign origin; Cush (or Ethiopia), the name of a son of Ham, and of his territory; also of an Israelite: Chush, Cush, Ethiopia.
  3569. Kuwshiy patronymically from Kuwsh; a Cushite, or descendant of Cush: Cushi, Cushite, Ethiopian(-s).
  3570. Kuwshiy the same as Kuwshiy; Cushi, the name of two Israelites: Cushi.
  3571. Kuwshiyth feminine of Kuwshiy; a Cushite woman: -Ethiopian.
  3572. Kuwshan perhaps from Kuwsh; Cushan, a region of Arabia: -Cushan.
  3573. Kuwshan Rish`athayim apparently from Kuwshan and the dual of rish`ah; Cushan of double wickedness; Cushan-Rishathajim, a Mesopotamian king: Chushan-rishathayim.
  3574. kowsharah from kasher; prosperity; in plural freedom: -X chain.
  3575. Kuwth or (feminine) Kuwthah; of foreign origin; Cuth or Cuthah, a province of Assyria: Cuth.
  3576. kazab a primitive root; to lie (i.e. deceive), literally or figuratively: fail, (be found a, make a) liar, lie, lying, be in vain.
  3577. kazab from kazab; falsehood; literally (untruth) or figuratively (idol): deceitful, false, leasing, + liar, lie, lying.
  3578. Kozba' from kazab; fallacious; Cozeba, a place in Palestine: Choseba.
  3579. Kozbiy from kazab; false; Cozbi, a Midianitess: Cozbi.
  3580. Kziyb from kazab; falsified; Kezib, a place in Palestine: Chezib.
  3581. koach or (Dan. 11:6) kowach; from an unused root meaning to be firm; vigor, literally (force, in a good or a bad sense) or figuratively (capacity, means, produce); also (from its hardiness) a large lizard: -ability, able, chameleon, force, fruits, might, power(-ful), strength, substance, wealth.
  3582. kachad a primitive root; to secrete, by act or word; hence (intensively) to destroy: conceal, cut down (off), desolate, hide.
  3583. kachal a primitive root; to paint (with stibium): -paint.
  3584. kachash a primitive root; to be untrue, in word (to lie, feign, disown) or deed (to disappoint, fail, cringe): deceive, deny, dissemble, fail, deal falsely, be found liars, (be-)lie, lying, submit selves.
  3585. kachash from kachash; literally, a failure of flesh, i.e. emaciation; figuratively, hypocrisy: leanness, lies, lying.
  3586. kechash from kachash; faithless: lying.
  3587. kiy from kavah; a brand or scar: burning.
  3588. kiy a primitive particle (the full form of the prepositional prefix) indicating causal relations of all kinds, antecedent or consequent; (by implication) very widely used as a relative conjunction or adverb (as below); often largely modified by other particles annexed: and, + (forasmuch, inasmuch, where-)as, assured(-ly), + but, certainly, doubtless, + else, even, + except, for, how, (because, in, so, than) that, + nevertheless, now, rightly, seeing, since, surely, then, therefore, + (al-)though, + till, truly, + until, when, whether, while, whom, yea, yet.
  3589. kiyd from a primitive root meaning to strike: a crushing; figuratively, calamity: destruction.
  3590. kiydowd from the same as kiyd (compare kadkod); properly, something struck off, i.e. a spark (as struck): spark.
  3591. kiydown from the same as kiyd; properly, something to strike with, i.e. a dart (perhaps smaller that chaniyth): lance, shield, spear, target.
  3592. Kiydown the same as kiydown; Kidon, a place in Palestine: -Chidon.
  3593. kiydowr of uncertain derivation; perhaps tumult: battle.
  3594. Kiyuwn from kuwn; properly, a statue, i.e. idol; but used (by euphemism) for some heathen deity (perhaps corresponding to Priapus or Baal-peor): Chiun.
  3595. kiyowr or kiyor; from the same as kuwr; properly, something round (as excavated or bored), i.e. a chafing-dish for coals or a caldron for cooking; hence (from similarity of form) a washbowl; also (for the same reason) a pulpit or platform: hearth, laver, pan, scaffold.
  3596. kiylay or kelay; from kuwl in the sense of withholding; niggardly: churl.
  3597. keylaph from an unused root meaning to clap or strike with noise; a club or sledge-hammer: hammer.
  3598. Kiymah from the same as kuwmaz; a cluster of stars, i.e. the Pleiades: Pleiades, seven stars.
  3599. kiyc a form for kowc; a cup; also a bag for money or weights: bag, cup, purse.
  3600. kiyr a form for kuwr (only in the dual); a cooking range (consisting of two parallel stones, across which the boiler is set): -ranges for pots.
  3601. kiyshowr from kasher; literally, a director, i.e. the spindle or shank of a distaff (pelek), by which it is twirled: spindle.
  3602. kakah from koh; just so, referring to the previous or following context: after that (this) manner, this matter, (even) so, in such a case, thus.
  3603. kikkar from karar; a circle, i.e. (by implication) a circumjacent tract or region, expec. the Ghor or valley of the Jordan; also a (round) loaf; also a talent (or large (round) coin): loaf, morsel, piece, plain, talent.
  3604. kikker (Aramaic) corresponding to kikkar; a talent: talent.
  3605. kol or (Jer. 33:8) kowl; from kalal; properly, the whole; hence, all, any or every (in the singular only, but often in a plural sense): (in) all (manner, (ye)), altogether, any (manner), enough, every (one, place, thing), howsoever, as many as, (no-)thing, ought, whatsoever, (the) whole, whoso(-ever).
  3606. kol (Aramaic) corresponding to kol: all, any, + (forasmuch) as, + be-(for this) cause, every, + no (manner, -ne), + there (where)-fore, + though, what (where, who)-soever, (the) whole.
  3607. kala' a primitive root; to restrict, by act (hold back or in) or word (prohibit): finish, forbid, keep (back), refrain, restrain, retain, shut up, be stayed, withhold.
  3608. kele' from kala'; a prison: prison. Compare kil'ayim, kliy'.
  3609. Kil'ab apparently from kala' and 'ab; restraint of (his) father; Kilab, an Israelite: Chileab.
  3610. kil'ayim dual of kele' in the original sense of separation; two heterogeneities: divers seeds (-e kinds), mingled (seed).
  3611. keleb from an unused root means. to yelp, or else to attack; a dog; hence (by euphemism) a male prostitute: dog.
  3612. Kaleb perhaps a form of keleb, or else from the same root in the sense of forcible; Caleb, the name of three Israelites: Caleb.
  3613. Kaleb 'Ephrathah from Kaleb and 'Ephraath; Caleb- Ephrathah, a place in Egypt (if the text is correct): Caleb-ephrathah.
  3614. Kalibbow probably by erroneous transcription for Kalebiy; patronymically from Kaleb; a Calebite or descendant of Caleb: of the house of Caleb.
  3615. kalah a primitive root; to end, whether intransitive (to cease, be finished, perish) or transitived (to complete, prepare, consume): accomplish, cease, consume (away), determine, destroy (utterly), be (when... were) done, (be an) end (of), expire, (cause to) fail, faint, finish, fulfil, X fully, X have, leave (off), long, bring to pass, wholly reap, make clean riddance, spend, quite take away, waste.
  3616. kaleh from kalah; pining: fail.
  3617. kalah from kalah; a completion; adverb, completely; also destruction: altogether, (be, utterly) consume(-d), consummation(-ption), was determined, (full, utter) end, riddance.
  3618. kallah from kalal; a bride (as if perfect); hence, a son's wife: bride, daughter-in-law, spouse.
  3619. klub from the same as keleb; a bird-trap (as furnished with a clap-stick or treadle to spring it); hence, a basket (as resembling a wicker cage): basket, cage.
  3620. Kluwb the same as klub; Kelub, the name of two Israelites: Chelub.
  3621. Kluwbay a form of Kaleb; Kelubai, an Israelite: -Chelubai.
  3622. Kluwhay from kalah; completed; Keluhai, an Israelite: Chelluh.
  3623. kluwlah denominative passive participle from kallah; bridehood (only in the plural): espousal.
  3624. kelach from an unused root meaning to be complete; maturity: full (old) age.
  3625. Kelach the same as kelach; Kelach, a place in Assyria: -Calah.
  3626. Kol-Chozeh from kol and chozeh; every seer; Col- Chozeh, an Israelite: Col-hozeh.
  3627. kliy from kalah; something prepared, i.e. any apparatus (as an implement, utensil, dress, vessel or weapon): armour ((-bearer)), artillery, bag, carriage, + furnish, furniture, instrument, jewel, that is made of, X one from another, that which pertaineth, pot, + psaltery, sack, stuff, thing, tool, vessel, ware, weapon, + whatsoever.
  3628. kliy' or kluw1; from kala' (compare kele'); a prison: prison.
  3629. kilyah feminine of kliy (only in the plural); a kidney (as an essential organ); figuratively, the mind (as the interior self): kidneys, reins.
  3630. Kilyown a form of killayown; Kiljon, an Israelite: Chilion.
  3631. killayown from kalah; pining, destruction: -consumption, failing.
  3632. kaliyl from kalal; complete; as noun, the whole (specifically, a sacrifice entirely consumed); as adverb, fully: all, every whit, flame, perfect(-ion), utterly, whole burnt offering (sacrifice), wholly.
  3633. Kalkol from kuwl; sustenance; Calcol, an Israelite: Calcol, Chalcol.
  3634. kalal a primitive root; to complete: (make) perfect.
  3635. klal (Aramaic) corresponding to kalal; to complete: finish, make (set) up.
  3636. Klal from kalal; complete; Kelal, an Israelite: Chelal.
  3637. kalam a primitive root; properly, to wound; but only figuratively, to taunt or insult: be (make) ashamed, blush, be confounded, be put to confusion, hurt, reproach, (do, put to) shame.
  3638. Kilmad of foreign derivation; Kilmad, a place apparently in the Assyrian empire: Chilmad.
  3639. klimmah from kalam; disgrace: confusion, dishonour, reproach, shame.
  3640. klimmuwth from klimmah; disgrace: shame.
  3641. Kalneh or Kalneh; also Kalnow; of foreign derivation; Calneh or Calno, a place in the Assyrian empire: Calneh, Calno. Compare Kanneh.
  3642. kamahh a primitive root; to pine after: long.
  3643. Kimham from kamahh; pining; Kimham, an Israelite: Chimham.
  3644. kmow or kamow; a form of the prefix "k-", but used separately (compare ken); as, thus, so: according to, (such) as (it were, well as), in comparison of, like (as, to, unto), thus, when, worth.
  3645. Kmowsh or (Jer. 48:7) Kmiysh; from an unused root meaning to subdue; the powerful; Kemosh, the god of the Moabites: Chemosh.
  3646. kammon from an unused root meaning to store up or preserve; "cummin" (from its use as a condiment): cummin.
  3647. kamac a primitive root; to store away, i.e. (figuratively) in the memory: lay up in store.
  3648. kamar a primitive root; properly, to intertwine or contract, i.e. (by implication) to shrivel (as with heat); figuratively, to be deeply affected with passion (love or pity): be black, be kindled, yearn.
  3649. kamar from kamar; properly, an ascetic (as if shrunk with self-maceration), i.e. an idolatrous priest (only in plural): Chemarims (idolatrous) priests.
  3650. kimriyr redupl. from kamar; obscuration (as if from shrinkage of light, i.e. an eclipse (only in plural): blackness.
  3651. ken from kuwn; properly, set upright; hence (figuratively as adjective) just; but usually (as adverb or conjunction) rightly or so (in various applications to manner, time and relation; often with other particles): + after that (this, -ward, -wards), as... as, + (for-)asmuch as yet, + be (for which) cause, + following, howbeit, in (the) like (manner, -wise), X the more, right, (even) so, state, straightway, such (thing), surely, + there (where)-fore, this, thus, true, well, X you.
  3652. ken (Aramaic) corresponding to ken; so: thus.
  3653. ken the same as ken, used as a noun; a stand, i.e. pedestal or station: base, estate, foot, office, place, well.
  3654. ken from kanan in the sense of fastening; a gnat (from infixing its sting; used only in plural (and irreg. in Exod. 8:17,18; Heb. 13:14)): lice, X manner.
  3655. kanah a primitive root; to address by an additional name; hence, to eulogize: give flattering titles, surname (himself).
  3656. Kanneh for Kalneh; Canneh, a place in Assyria: Canneh.
  3657. kannah from kanan; a plant (as set): X vineyard.
  3658. kinnowr from a unused root meaning to twang; a harp: -harp.
  3659. Konyahuw for Ykonyah; Conjah, an Israelite king: Coniah.
  3660. knema' (Aramaic) corresponding to kmow; so or thus: so, (in) this manner (sort), thus.
  3661. kanan a primitive root; to set out, i.e. plant: X vineyard.
  3662. Knaniy from kanan; planted; Kenani, an Israelite: -Chenani.
  3663. Knanyah or Knanyahuw; from kanan and Yahh; Jah has planted; Kenanjah, an Israelite: Chenaniah.
  3664. kanac a primitive root; to collect; hence, to enfold: -gather (together), heap up, wrap self.
  3665. kana` a primitive root; properly, to bend the knee; hence, to humiliate, vanquish: bring down (low), into subjection, under, humble (self), subdue.
  3666. kin`ah from kana` in the sense of folding (compare kanac); a package: wares.
  3667. Kna`an from kana`; humiliated; Kenaan, a son a Ham; also the country inhabited by him: Canaan, merchant, traffick.
  3668. Kna`anah feminine of Kna`an; Kenaanah, the name of two Israelites: Chenaanah.
  3669. Kna`aniy patrial from Kna`an; a Kenaanite or inhabitant of Kenaan; by implication, a pedlar (the Canaanites standing for their neighbors the Ishmaelites, who conducted mercantile caravans): Canaanite, merchant, trafficker.
  3670. kanaph a primitive root; properly, to project laterally, i.e. probably (reflexive) to withdraw: be removed.
  3671. kanaph from kanaph; an edge or extremity; specifically (of a bird or army) a wing, (of a garment or bed-clothing) a flap, (of the earth) a quarter, (of a building) a pinnacle: + bird, border, corner, end, feather(-ed), X flying, + (one an-)other, overspreading, X quarters, skirt, X sort, uttermost part, wing((-ed)).
  3672. Kinnrowth or Kinnereth; respectively plural and singular feminine from the same as kinnowr; perhaps harp-shaped; Kinneroth or Kinnereth, a place in Palestine: Chinnereth, Chinneroth, Cinneroth.
  3673. kanash (Aramaic) corresponding to kanac; to assemble: gather together.
  3674. knath from kanah; a colleague (as having the same title): companion.
  3675. knath (Aramaic) corresponding to knath: companion.
  3676. kec apparently a contraction for kicce', but probably by erroneous transcription for nec: sworn.
  3677. kece' or keceh; apparently from kacah; properly, fulness or the full moon, i.e. its festival: (time) appointed.
  3678. kicce' or kicceh; from kacah; properly, covered, i.e. a throne (as canopied): seat, stool, throne.
  3679. Kacday for Kasdiy: Chaldean.
  3680. kacah a primitive root; properly, to plump, i.e. fill up hollows; by implication, to cover (for clothing or secrecy): clad self, close, clothe, conceal, cover (self), (flee to) hide, overwhelm. Compare kasah.
  3681. kacuwy passive participle of kacah; properly, covered, i.e. (as noun) a covering: covering.
  3682. kcuwth from kacah; a cover (garment); figuratively, a veiling: covering, raiment, vesture.
  3683. kacach a primitive root; to cut off: cut down (up).
  3684. kciyl from kacal; properly, fat, i.e. (figuratively) stupid or silly: fool(-ish).
  3685. Kciyl the same as kciyl; any notable constellation; specifically Orion (as if a burly one): constellation, Orion.
  3686. Kciyl the same as kciyl; Kesil, a place in Palestine: -Chesil.
  3687. kciyluwth from kciyl; silliness: foolish.
  3688. kacal a primitive root; properly, to be fat, i.e. (figuratively) silly: be foolish.
  3689. kecel from kacal; properly, fatness, i.e. by implication (literally) the loin (as the seat of the leaf fat) or (generally) the viscera; also (figuratively) silliness or (in a good sense) trust: confidence, flank, folly, hope, loin.
  3690. kiclah feminine of kecel; in a good sense, trust; in a bad one, silliness: confidence, folly.

  3695. Kacluchiym a plural probably of foreign derivation; Casluchim, a people cognate to the Egyptians: Casluhim.
  3696. Kicloth Tabor from the feminine plural of kecel and Tabowr; flanks of Tabor; Kisloth-Tabor, a place in Palestine: Chisloth- tabor.
  3697. kacam a primitive root; to shear: X only, poll. Compare kircem.
  3698. kuccemeth from kacam; spelt (from its bristliness as if just shorn): fitches, rie.
  3699. kacac a primitive root; to estimate: make count.
  3700. kacaph a primitive root; properly, to become pale, i.e. (by implication) to pine after; also to fear: (have) desire, be greedy, long, sore.
  3701. keceph from kacaph; silver (from its pale color); by implication, money: money, price, silver(-ling).
  3702. kcaph (Aramaic) corresponding to keceph: money, silver.
  3703. Kaciphya' perhaps from keceph; silvery; Casiphja, a place in Bab.: Casiphia.
  3704. keceth from kacah; a cushion or pillow (as covering a seat or bed): pillow.

  3707. ka`ac a primitive root; to trouble; by implication, to grieve, rage, be indignant: be angry, be grieved, take indignation, provoke (to anger, unto wrath), have sorrow, vex, be wroth.
  3708. ka`ac or (in Job) kaoas; from ka`ac; vexation: -anger, angry, grief, indignation, provocation, provoking, X sore, sorrow, spite, wrath.
  3709. kaph from kaphaph; the hollow hand or palm (so of the paw of an animal, of the sole, and even of the bowl of a dish or sling, the handle of a bolt, the leaves of a palm-tree); figuratively, power: branch, + foot, hand((-ful), -dle, (-led)), hollow, middle, palm, paw, power, sole, spoon.

  3713. kphowr from kaphar; properly, a cover, i.e. (by implication) a tankard (or covered goblet); also white frost (as covering the ground): bason, hoar(-y) frost.
  3714. kaphiyc from an unused root meaning to connect; a girder: beam.

  3716. Kphiyrah feminine of kphiyr; the village (always with the art.); Kephirah, a place in Palestine: Chephirah.

  3723. kaphar from kaphar; a village (as protected by walls): -village. Compare kphiyr.
  3724. kopher from kaphar; properly, a cover, i.e. (literally) a village (as covered in); (specifically) bitumen (as used for coating), and the henna plant (as used for dyeing); figuratively, a redemption-price: bribe, camphire, pitch, ransom, satisfaction, sum of money, village.

  3727. kapporeth from kaphar; a lid (used only of the cover of the sacred Ark): mercy seat.

  3729. kphath (Aramaic) a root of uncertain correspondence; to fetter: bind.
  3730. kaphtor or (Am. 9:1) kaphtowr; probably from an unused root meaning to encircle; a chaplet; but used only in an architectonic sense, i.e. the capital of a column, or a wreath-like button or disk on the candelabrum: knop, (upper) lintel.
  3731. Kaphtor or (Am. 9:7) Kaphtowr; apparently the same as kaphtor; Caphtor (i.e. a wreath-shaped island), the original seat of the Philistines: Caphtor.

  3799. katham a primitive root; properly, to carve or engrave, i.e. (by implication) to inscribe indelibly: mark.
  3800. kethem from katham; properly, something carved out, i.e. ore; hence, gold (pure as originally mined): ((most) fine, pure) gold(-en wedge).
  3801. kthoneth or kuttoneth; from an unused root meaning to cover (compare katheph); a shirt: coat, garment, robe.
  3802. katheph from an unused root meaning to clothe; the shoulder (proper, i.e. upper end of the arm; as being the spot where the garments hang); figuratively, side-piece or lateral projection of anything: arm, corner, shoulder(-piece), side, undersetter.
  3803. kathar a primitive root; to enclose; hence (in a friendly sense) to crown, (in a hostile one) to besiege; also to wait (as restraining oneself): beset round, compass about, be crowned inclose round, suffer.

  3806. kathash a primitive root; to butt or pound: bray.
  3807. kathath a primitive root; to bruise or violently strike: beat (down, to pieces), break in pieces, crushed, destroy, discomfit, smite, stamp.
  3808. lo' or lowi; or loh (Deut. 3:11); a primitive particle; not (the simple or abs. negation); by implication, no; often used with other particles (as follows): X before, + or else, ere, + except, ig(-norant), much, less, nay, neither, never, no((-ne), -r, (-thing)), (X as though...,(can-), for) not (out of), of nought, otherwise, out of, + surely, + as truly as, + of a truth, + verily, for want, + whether, without.
  3809. la' (Aramaic) or lah (Aramaic) (Dan. 4:32); corresponding to lo': or even, neither, no(-ne, -r), ((can-))not, as nothing, without.
  3810. Lo' Dbar or Low Dbar (2 Samuel 9:4,5); or Lidbir (Joshua 13:26); (probably rather Lodbar); from lo' and dober; pastureless; Lo-Debar, a place in Palestine: Debir, Lo-debar.

  3820. leb a form of lebab; the heart; also used (figuratively) very widely for the feelings, the will and even the intellect; likewise for the centre of anything: + care for, comfortably, consent, X considered, courag(-eous), friend(-ly), ((broken-), (hard-), (merry-), (stiff-), (stout-), double) heart((-ed)), X heed, X I, kindly, midst, mind(-ed), X regard((-ed)), X themselves, X unawares, understanding, X well, willingly, wisdom.

  4100. mah or mah; or ma; or ma; also meh; a primitive particle; properly, interrogative what? (including how? why? when?); but also exclamation, what! (including how!), or indefinitely what (including whatever, and even relatively, that which); often used with prefixes in various adverbial or conjunctive senses: how (long, oft, (- soever)), (no-)thing, what (end, good, purpose, thing), whereby(-fore, -in, -to, -with), (for) why.
  4101. mah (Aramaic) corresponding to mah: how great (mighty), that which, what(-soever), why.

  4664. miphrats from parats; a break (in the shore), i.e. a haven: breach.

  4671. mots or mowts (Zephaniah 2:2); from muwts; chaff (as pressed out, i.e. winnowed or (rather) threshed loose): chaff.
  4672. matsa' a primitive root; properly, to come forth to, i.e. appear or exist; transitively, to attain, i.e. find or acquire; figuratively, to occur, meet or be present: + be able, befall, being, catch, X certainly, (cause to) come (on, to, to hand), deliver, be enough (cause to) find(-ing, occasion, out), get (hold upon), X have (here), be here, hit, be left, light (up-)on, meet (with), X occasion serve, (be) present, ready, speed, suffice, take hold on.
  4673. matstsab from natsab; a fixed spot; figuratively, an office, a military post: garrison, station, place where...stood.

  4677. Mtsobayah apparently from matsa' and Yahh; found of Jah; Metsobajah, a place in Palestine: Mesobaite.
  4678. matstsebeth from natsab; something stationary, i.e. a monumental stone; also the stock of a tree: pillar, substance.
  4679. mtsad or mtsad; or (feminine) mtsadah; from tsuwd; a fastness (as a covert of ambush): castle, fort, (strong) hold, munition.

  4682. matstsah from matsats in the sense of greedily devouring for sweetness; properly, sweetness; concretely, sweet (i.e. not soured or bittered with yeast); specifically, an unfermented cake or loaf, or (elliptically) the festival of Passover (because no leaven was then used): unleaved (bread, cake), without leaven.
  4683. matstsah from natsah; a quarrel: contention, debate, strife.
  4684. matshalah from tsahal; a whinnying (through impatience for battle or lust): neighing.

  4686. matsuwd or (feminine) mtsuwdah; or mtsudah; for matsowd; a net, or (abstractly) capture; also a fastness; --castle, defense, fort(-ress), (strong) hold, be hunted, net, snare, strong place.

  4726. maqowr or maqor; from quwr; properly, something dug, i.e. a (general) source (of water, even when naturally flowing; also of tears, blood (by euphemism, of the female pudenda); figuratively, of happiness, wisdom, progeny): fountain, issue, spring, well(-spring).
  4727. miqqach from laqach; reception: taking.

  4743. maqaq ' a primitive root; to melt; figuratively, to flow, dwindle, vanish: consume away, be corrupt, dissolve, pine away.
  4744. miqra' from qara'; something called out, i.e. a public meeting (the act, the persons, or the place); also a rehearsal: assembly, calling, convocation, reading.

  5064. nagar a primitive root; to flow; figuratively, to stretch out; causatively, to pour out or down; figuratively, to deliver over: fall, flow away, pour down (out), run, shed, spilt, trickle down.
  5065. nagas a primitive root; to drive (an animal, a workman, a debtor, an army); by implication, to tax, harass, tyrannize: distress, driver, exact(-or), oppress(-or), X raiser of taxes, taskmaster.
  5066. nagash a primitive root; to be or come (causatively, bring) near (for any purpose); euphemistically, to lie with a woman; as an enemy, to attack; relig. to worship; causatively, to present; figuratively, to adduce an argument; by reversal, to stand back: (make to) approach (nigh), bring (forth, hither, near), (cause to) come (hither, near, nigh), give place, go hard (up), (be, draw, go) near (nigh), offer, overtake, present, put, stand.
  5067. ned from nuwd in the sense of piling up; a mound, i.e. wave: heap.
  5068. nadab a primitive root; to impel; hence, to volunteer (as a soldier), to present spontaneously: offer freely, be (give, make, offer self) willing(-ly).
  5069. ndab (Aramaic) corresponding to nadab; be (or give) liberal(-ly): (be minded of...own) freewill (offering), offer freely (willingly).
  5070. Nadab from nadab; liberal; Nadab, the name of four Israelites: Nadab.
  5071. ndabah from nadab; properly (abstractly) spontaneity, or (adjectively) spontaneous; also (concretely) a spontaneous or (by inference, in plural) abundant gift: free(-will) offering, freely, plentiful, voluntary(-ily, offering), willing(-ly), offering).
  5072. Ndabyah from nadab and Yahh; largess of Jah; Nedabjah, an Israelite: Nedabiah.
  5073. nidbak (Aramaic) from a root meaning to stick; a layer (of building materials): row.
  5074. nadad a primitive root; properly, to wave to and fro (rarely to flap up and down); figuratively, to rove, flee, or (causatively) to drive away: chase (away), X could not, depart, flee (X apace, away), (re-)move, thrust away, wander (abroad, -er, -ing).
  5075. ndad (Aramaic) corresponding to nadad; to depart: go from.
  5076. nadud passive participle of nadad; properly, tossed; abstractly, a rolling (on the bed): tossing to and fro.
  5077. nadah or nada (2 Kings 17:21); a primitive root; properly, to toss; figuratively, to exclude, i.e. banish, postpone, prohibit: cast out, drive, put far away.
  5078. nedeh from nadah in the sense of freely flinging money; a bounty (for prostitution): gifts.
  5079. niddah from nadad; properly, rejection; by implication, impurity, especially personal (menstruation) or moral (idolatry, incest): X far, filthiness, X flowers, menstruous (woman), put apart, X removed (woman), separation, set apart, unclean(-ness, thing, with filthiness).
  5080. nadach a primitive root; to push off; used in a great variety of applications, literally and figuratively (to expel, mislead, strike, inflict, etc.): banish, bring, cast down (out), chase, compel, draw away, drive (away, out, quite), fetch a stroke, force, go away, outcast, thrust away (out), withdraw.
  5081. nadiyb from nadab; properly, voluntary, i.e. generous; hence, magnanimous; as noun, a grandee (sometimes a tyrant): free, liberal (things), noble, prince, willing ((hearted)).
  5082. ndiybah feminine of nadiyb; properly, nobility, i.e. reputation: soul.
  5083. nadan probably from an unused root meaning to give; a present (for prostitution): gift.
  5084. nadan of uncertain derivation; a sheath (of a sword): sheath.
  5085. nidneh (Aramaic) from the same as nadan; a sheath; figuratively, the body (as the receptacle of the soul): body.
  5086. nadaph a primitive root; to shove asunder, i.e. disperse: drive (away, to and fro), thrust down, shaken, tossed to and fro.
  5087. nadar a primitive root; to promise (pos., to do or give something to God): (make a) vow.

  5089. noahh from an unused root meaning to lament; lamentation: wailing.
  5090. nahag a primitive root; to drive forth (a person, an animal or chariot), i.e. lead, carry away; reflexively, to proceed (i.e. impel or guide oneself); also (from the panting induced by effort), to sigh: acquaint, bring (away), carry away, drive (away), lead (away, forth), (be) guide, lead (away, forth).
  5091. nahah a primitive root; to groan, i.e. bewail; hence (through the idea of crying aloud), to assemble (as if on proclamation): lament, wail.
  5092. nhiy from nahah; an elegy: lamentation, wailing.
  5093. nihyah feminine of nhiy; lamentation: doleful.
  5094. nhiyr (Aramaic) or nehiyruw (Aramaic); from the same as nharah; illumination, i.e. (figuratively) wisdom: light.
  5095. nahal a primitive root; properly, to run with a sparkle, i.e. flow; hence (transitively), to conduct, and (by inference) to protect, sustain: carry, feed, guide, lead (gently, on).
  5096. Nahalal or Nahalol; the same as nahalol; Nahalal or Nahalol, a place in Palestine: Nahalal, Nahallal, Nahalol.

  5102. nahar a primitive root; to sparkle, i.e. (figuratively) be cheerful; hence (from the sheen of a running stream) to flow, i.e. (figuratively) assemble: flow (together), be lightened.
  5103. nhar (Aramaic) from a root corresponding to nahar; a river, especially the Euphrates: river, stream.

  5105. nharah from nahar in its original sense; daylight: light.
  5106. nuw' a primitive root; to refuse, forbid, dissuade, or neutralize: break, disallow, discourage, make of none effect.

  5110. nuwd a primitive root; to nod, i.e. waver; figuratively, to wander, flee, disappear; also (from shaking the head in sympathy), to console, deplore, or (from tossing the head in scorn) taunt: bemoan, flee, get, mourn, make to move, take pity, remove, shake, skip for joy, be sorry, vagabond, way, wandering.
  5111. nuwd (Aramaic) corresponding to naveh; to flee: get away.

  5115. navah a primitive root; to rest (as at home); causatively (through the implied idea of beauty (compare naveh)), to celebrate (with praises): keept at home, prepare an habitation.
  5116. naveh or (feminine) navah; from navah; (adjectively) at home; hence (by implication of satisfaction) lovely; also (noun) a home, of God (temple), men (residence), flocks (pasture), or wild animals (den): comely, dwelling (place), fold, habitation, pleasant place, sheepcote, stable, tarried.
  5117. nuwach a primitive root; to rest, i.e. settle down; used in a great variety of applications, literal and figurative, intransitive, transitive and causative (to dwell, stay, let fall, place, let alone, withdraw, give comfort, etc.): cease, be confederate, lay, let down, (be) quiet, remain, (cause to, be at, give, have, make to) rest, set down.   5122. nvaluw (Aramaic) or nvaliy (Aramaic); from an unused root probably meaning to be foul; a sink: dunghill.

  5124. nuwmah from nuwm; sleepiness: drowsiness.
  5125. nuwn a primitive root; to resprout, i.e. propagate by shoots; figuratively, to be perpetual: be continued.
  5126. Nuwn or Nown (1 Chron. 7:27); from nuwn; perpetuity, Nun or Non, the father of Joshua: Non, Nun.

  5128. nuwa` a primitive root; to waver, in a great variety of applications, literally and figuratively (as subjoined): continually, fugitive, X make, to (go) up and down, be gone away, (be) move(-able, -d), be promoted, reel, remove, scatter, set, shake, sift, stagger, to and fro, be vagabond, wag, (make) wander (up and down).
  5129. Now`adyah from ya`ad and Yahh; convened of Jah; Noadjah, the name of an Israelite, and a false prophetess: Noadiah.

  5131. nowph from nuwph; elevation: situation. Compare Noph.
  5132. nuwts a primitive root; properly, to flash; hence, to blossom (from the brilliancy of color); also, to fly away (from the quickness of motion): flee away, bud (forth).
  5133. nowtsah or notsah; feminine active participle of natsah in the sense of flying; a pinion (or wing feather); often (collectively) plumage: feather(-s), ostrich.

  5138. naziyd from zuwd; something boiled, i.e. soup: pottage.

  5140. nazal a primitive root; to drip, or shed by trickling: distil, drop, flood, (cause to) flow(-ing), gush out, melt, pour (down), running water, stream.

  5144. nazar a primitive root; to hold aloof, i.e. (intransitivey) abstain (from food and drink, from impurity, and even from divine worship (i.e. apostatize)); specifically, to set apart (to sacred purposes), i.e. devote: consecrate, separate(-ing, self).
  5145. nezer or nezer; from nazar; properly, something set apart, i.e. (abstractly) dedication (of a priet or Nazirite); hence (concretely) unshorn locks; also (by implication) a chaplet (especially of royalty): consecration, crown, hair, separation.

  5158. nachal or (feminine) nachlah (Psalm 124:4); or nachalah (Ezekiel 47:19; 48:28); from nachal in its original sense; a stream, especially a winter torrent; (by implication) a (narrow) valley (in which a brook runs); also a shaft (of a mine): brook, flood, river, stream, valley.
  5159. nachalah from nachal (in its usual sense); properly, something inherited, i.e. (abstractly) occupancy, or (concretely) an heirloom; generally an estate, patrimony or portion: heritage, to inherit, inheritance, possession. Compare nachal.
  5160. Nachaliy'el from nachal and 'el; valley of God; Nachaliel, a place in the Desert: Nahaliel.

  5162. nacham a primitive root; properly, to sigh, i.e. breathe strongly; by implication, to be sorry, i.e. (in a favorable sense) to pity, console or (reflexively) rue; or (unfavorably) to avenge (oneself): comfort (self), ease (one's self), repent(-er,-ing, self).

  5258. nacak a primitive root; to pour out, especially a libation, or to cast (metal); by analogy, to anoint a king: cover, melt, offer, (cause to) pour (out), set (up).
  5259. nacak a primitive root (probably identical with nacak through the idea of fusion); to interweave, i.e. (figuratively) to overspread: that is spread.
  5260. ncak (Aramaic) corresponding to nacak; to pour out a libation: offer.
  5261. ncak (Aramaic) corresponding to necek; a libation: drink offering.
  5262. necek or necek; from nacak; a libation; also a cast idol: cover, drink offering, molten image.
  5263. nacac a primitive root; to wane, i.e. be sick: faint.
  5264. nacac a primitive root; to gleam from afar, i.e. to be conspicuous as a signal; or rather perhaps a denominative from nec (and identical with nacac, through the idea of a flag as fluttering in the wind); to raise a beacon: lift up as an ensign.
  5265. naca` a primitive root; properly, to pull up, especially the tent-pins, i.e. start on a journey: cause to blow, bring, get, (make to) go (away, forth, forward, onward, out), (take) journey, march, remove, set aside (forward), X still, be on his (go their) way.
  5266. nacaq a primitive root; to go up: ascend.
  5267. ncaq (Aramaic) corresponding to nacaq: take up.
  5268. Nicrok of foreign origin; Nisrok, a Babylonian idol: Nisroch.
  5269. Ne`ah from nuwa`; motion; Neah, a place in Palestine: Neah.
  5270. No`ah from nuwa`; movement; Noah, an Israelitess: Noah.
  5271. na`uwr or naur; and (feminine) nturah; properly, passive participle from na`ar as denominative; (only in plural collectively or emphatic form) youth, the state (juvenility) or the persons (young people): childhood, youth.
  5272. N`iy'el from nuwa` and 'el; moved of God; Neiel, a place in Palestine: Neiel.
  5273. na`iym from na`em; delightful (objective or subjective, literal or figurative): pleasant(-ure), sweet.
  5274. na`al a primitive root; properly, to fasten up, i.e. with a bar or cord; hence (denominative from na`al), to sandal, i.e. furnish with slippers: bolt, inclose, lock, shoe, shut up.
  5275. na`al or (feminine) na`alah; from na`al; properly, a sandal tongue; by extens. a sandal or slipper (sometimes as a symbol of occupancy, a refusal to marry, or of something valueless): dryshod, (pair of) shoe((-latchet), -s).
  5276. na`em a primitive root; to be agreeable (literally or figuratively): pass in beauty, be delight, be pleasant, be sweet.
  5277. Na`am from na`em; pleasure; Naam, an Israelite: Naam.
  5278. no`am from na`em; agreeableness, i.e. delight, suitableness, splendor or grace: beauty, pleasant(-ness).
  5279. Na`amah feminine of Na`am; pleasantness; Naamah, the name of an antediluvian woman, of an Ammonitess, and of a place in Palestine: Naamah.
  5280. Na`amiy patronymic from Na`aman; a Naamanite, or descendant of Naaman (collectively): Naamites.
  5281. No`omiy from no`am; pleasant; Noomi, an Israelitess: Naomi.
  5282. na`aman from na`em; pleasantness (plural as concrete): pleasant.
  5283. Na`aman the same as na`aman; Naaman, the name of an Israelite and of a Damascene: Naaman.
  5284. Na`amathiy patrial from a place corresponding in name (but not identical) with Na`amah; a Naamathite, or inhabitant of Naamah: Naamathite.
  5285. na`atsuwts from an unused root meaning to prick; probably a brier; by implication, a thicket of thorny bushes: thorn.
  5286. na`ar a primitive root; to growl: yell.
  5287. na`ar a primitive root (probably identical with na`ar, through the idea of the rustling of mane, which usually accompanies the lion's roar); to tumble about: shake (off, out, self), overthrow, toss up and down.
  5288. na`ar from na`ar; (concretely) a boy (as active), from the age of infancy to adolescence; by implication, a servant; also (by interch. of sex), a girl (of similar latitude in age): babe, boy, child, damsel (from the margin), lad, servant, young (man).
  5289. na`ar from na`ar in its derivative sense of tossing about; a wanderer: young one.
  5290. no`ar from na`ar; (abstractly) boyhood (compare na`ar): child, youth.
  5291. na`arah feminine of na`ar; a girl (from infancy to adolescence): damsel, maid(-en), young (woman).
  5292. Na`arah the same as na`arah; Naarah, the name of an Israelitess, and of a place in Palestine: Naarah, Naarath.
  5293. Na`aray from na`ar; youthful; Naarai, an Israelite: Naarai.
  5294. Ne`aryah from na`ar and Yahh; servant of Jah; Nearjah, the name of two Israelites: Neariah.
  5295. Na`aran from na`ar; juvenile; Naaran, a place in Palestine: Naaran.
  5296. n`oreth from na`ar; something shaken out, i.e. tow (as the refuse of flax): tow.

  5298. Nepheg from an unused root probably meaning to spring forth; a sprout; Nepheg, the name of two Israelites: Nepheg.

  5306. nophek from an unused root meaning to glisten; shining; a gem, probably the garnet: emerald.
  5307. naphal a primitive root; to fall, in a great variety of applications (intransitive or causative, literal or figurative): be accepted, cast (down, self, (lots), out), cease, die, divide (by lot), (let) fail, (cause to, let, make, ready to) fall (away, down, -en, -ing), fell(-ing), fugitive, have (inheritance), inferior, be judged (by mistake for palal), lay (along), (cause to) lie down, light (down), be (X hast) lost, lying, overthrow, overwhelm, perish, present(-ed, -ing), (make to) rot, slay, smite out, X surely, throw down.

  5309. nephel or nephel; from naphal; something fallen, i.e. an abortion: untimely birth.

  5313. niphqa' (Aramaic) from nphaq; an outgo, i.e. expense: expense.
  5314. naphash a primitive root; to breathe; passively, to be breathed upon, i.e. (figuratively) refreshed (as if by a current of air): (be) refresh selves (-ed).
  5315. nephesh from naphash; properly, a breathing creature, i.e. animal of (abstractly) vitality; used very widely in a literal, accommodated or figurative sense (bodily or mental): any, appetite, beast, body, breath, creature, X dead(-ly), desire, X (dis-)contented, X fish, ghost, + greedy, he, heart(-y), (hath, X jeopardy of) life (X in jeopardy), lust, man, me, mind, mortally, one, own, person, pleasure, (her-, him-, my-, thy-)self, them (your)-selves, + slay, soul, + tablet, they, thing, (X she) will, X would have it.

  5320. Naphtuchiym plural of foreign origin, Naphtuchim, an Egyptian tribe: Naptuhim.

  5327. natsah a primitive root; properly, to go forth, i.e. (by implication) to be expelled, and (consequently) desolate; causatively, to lay waste; also (specifically), to quarrel: be laid waste, runinous, strive (together).
  5328. nitstsah feminine of nets; a blossom; --flower.
  5329. natsach a primitive root; properly, to glitter from afar, i.e. to be eminent (as a superintendent, especially of the Temple services and its music); also (as denominative from netsach), to be permanent: excel, chief musician (singer), oversee(-r), set forward.
  5330. ntsach (Aramaic) corresponding to natsach; to become chief: be preferred.
  5331. netsach or netsach; from natsach; properly, a goal, i.e. the bright object at a distance travelled towards; hence (figuratively), splendor, or (subjectively) truthfulness, or (objectively) confidence; but usually (adverbially), continually (i.e. to the most distant point of view); --alway(-s), constantly, end, (+ n-)ever(more), perpetual, strength, victory.
  5332. Netsach probably identical with netsach, through the idea of brilliancy of color; juice of the grape (as blood red): blood, strength.
  5333. ntsiyb or ntsib; from natsab; something stationary, i.e. a prefect, a military post, a statue: garrison, officer, pillar.

  5674. `abar a primitive root; to cross over; used very widely of any transition (literal or figurative; transitive, intransitive, intensive, causative); specifically, to cover (in copulation): alienate, alter, X at all, beyond, bring (over, through), carry over, (over-)come (on, over), conduct (over), convey over, current, deliver, do away, enter, escape, fail, gender, get over, (make) go (away, beyond, by, forth, his way, in, on, over, through), have away (more), lay, meddle, overrun, make partition, (cause to, give, make to, over) pass(-age, along, away, beyond, by, -enger, on, out, over, through), (cause to, make) + proclaim(-amation), perish, provoke to anger, put away, rage, + raiser of taxes, remove, send over, set apart, + shave, cause to (make) sound, X speedily, X sweet smelling, take (away), (make to) transgress(-or), translate, turn away, (way-)faring man, be wrath.
  5675. `abar (Aramaic) corresponding to `eber: beyond, this side.
  5676. `eber from `abar; properly, a region across; but used only adverbially (with or without a preposition) on the opposite side (especially of the Jordan; ususally meaning the east): X against, beyond, by, X from, over, passage, quarter, (other, this) side, straight.
  5677. `Eber the same as `eber; Eber, the name of two patriarchs and four Israelites: Eber, Heber.
  5678. `ebrah feminine of `eber; an outburst of passion: anger, rage, wrath.
  5679. `abarah from `abar; a crossing-place: ferry, plain (from the margin).
  5680. `Ibriy patronymic from `Eber; an Eberite (i.e. Hebrew) or descendant of Eber: Hebrew(-ess, woman).
  5681. `Ibriy the same as `Ibriy; Ibri, an Israelite: Ibri.
  5682. `Abarim plural of `eber; regions beyond; Abarim, a place in Palestine: Abarim, passages.
  5683. `Ebron from `eber; transitional; Ebron, a place in Palestine: Hebron. Perhaps a clerical error for `Abdown.
  5684. `Ebronah feminine of `Ebron; Ebronah, place in the Desert: Ebronah.
  5685. `abash a primitive root; to dry up: be rotten.
  5686. `abath a primitive root; to interlace, i.e. (figuratively) to pervert: wrap up.
  5687. `aboth or rabowth; from `abath; intwined, i.e. dense: thick.
  5688. `aboth or rabowth; or (feminine) tabothah; the same as `aboth; something intwined, i.e. a string, wreath or foliage: band, cord, rope, thick bough (branch), wreathen (chain).
  5689. `agab a primitive root; to breathe after, i.e. to love (sensually): dote, lover.
  5690. `egeb from `agab; love (concretely), i.e. amative words: much love, very lovely.
  5691. `agabah from `agab; love (abstractly), i.e. amorousness: inordinate love.
  5692. `uggah from `uwg; an ash-cake (as round): cake (upon the hearth).
  5693. `aguwr passive part (but with active sense) of an unused root meaning to twitter: probably the swallow: swallow.
  5694. `agiyl from the same as `agol; something round, i.e. a ring (for the ears): earring.
  5695. `egel from the same as `agol; a (male) calf (as frisking round), especially one nearly grown (i.e. a steer): bullock, calf.
  5696. `agol or magowl; from an unused root meaning to revolve, circular: round.
  5697. `eglah feminine of `egel; a (female) calf, especially one nearly grown (i.e. a heifer): calf, cow, heifer.
  5698. `Eglah the same as `eglah; Eglah, a wife of David: Eglah.
  5699. `agalah from the same as `agol; something revolving, i.e. a wheeled vehicle:--cart, chariot, wagon
  5700. `Eglown from `egel; vituline; Eglon, the name of a place in Palestine and of a Moabitish king: Eglon.
  5701. `agam a primitive root; to be sad: grieve.
  5702. `agan a primitive root; to debar, i.e. from marriage: stay.
  5703. `ad from `adah; properly, a (peremptory) terminus, i.e. (by implication) duration, in the sense of advance or perpetuity (substantially as a noun, either with or without a preposition): eternity, ever(- lasting, -more), old, perpetually, + world without end.
  5704. `ad properly, the same as `ad (used as a preposition, adverb or conjunction; especially with a preposition); as far (or long, or much) as, whether of space (even unto) or time (during, while, until) or degree (equally with): against, and, as, at, before, by (that), even (to), for(-asmuch as), (hither-)to, + how long, into, as long (much) as, (so) that, till, toward, until, when, while, (+ as) yet.
  5705. `ad (Aramaic) corresponding to `ad; X and, at, for, (hither-)to, on till, (un-)to, until, within.
  5706. `ad the same as `ad in the sense of the aim of an attack; booty: prey.
  5707. `ed contracted from `uwd; concretely, a witness; abstractly, testimony; specifically, a recorder, i.e. prince: witness.
  5708. `ed from an unused root meaning to set a period (compare `adah, `uwd); the menstrual flux (as periodical); by implication (in plural) soiling: filthy.
  5709. `ada' (Aramaic) or adah (Aramaic); corresponding to `adah: alter, depart, pass (away), remove, take (away).
  5710. `adah a primitive root; to advance, i.e. pass on or continue; causatively, to remove; specifically, to bedeck (i.e. bring an ornament upon): adorn, deck (self), pass by, take away.
  5711. `Adah from `adah; ornament; Adah, the name of two women: Adah.
  5712. `edah feminine of `ed in the original sense of fixture; a stated assemblage (specifically, a concourse, or generally, a family or crowd): assembly, company, congregation, multitude, people, swarm. Compare `edah.
  5713. `edah feminine of `ed in its techn. sense; testimony: testimony, witness. Compare `edah.
  5714. `Iddow or Iddowo; or Iddiy; from `adah; timely; Iddo (or Iddi), the name of five Israelites: Iddo. Compare Yiddow, Y`diy.
  5715. `eduwth feminine of `ed; testimony: testimony, witness.
  5716. `adiy from `adah in the sense of trappings; finery; generally an outfit; specifically, a headstall: X excellent, mouth, ornament.

  5718. `Adayah or Adayahuw; from `adah and Yahh; Jah has adorned; Adajah, the name of eight Israelites: Adaiah.
  5719. `adiyn from `adan; voluptuous: given to pleasures.

  5723. `Adiythayim dual of a feminine of `ad; double prey; Adithajim, a place in Palestine: Adithaim.

  5726. `Adullamiy patrial from `Adullam; an Adullamite or native of Adullam: Adullamite.
  5727. `adan a primitive root; to be soft or pleasant; figuratively and reflexively, to live voluptuously: delight self.

  5731. `Eden the same as `eden (masculine); Eden, the region of Adam's home: Eden.
  5732. `iddan (Aramaic) from a root corresponding to that of `ed; a set time; technically, a year: time.
